                        <th width="100%" height="439" valign="top" scope="row"><h2>Administration & coordination</h2>
                          <p>The administration and coordination section  consists of two members, which are also the founders of the project: <br>
                            <strong>Bernd  Hoffmann</strong>, Federal Office for Radiation Protection,  Berlin, Germany.<br>
Bernd Hoffmann got a PhD in Physics and  work as a scientist at the German Federal Office for Radiation Protection. He  is the head of the section &quot;Radon&quot; as well as of the section  &quot;Natural occurring radioactive materials and residues&quot;. Since almost  20 years, he is specialized in the fields of Radon and radioactivity in  building materials and advice the German government about strategies,  techniques and solutions. He is working in corresponding national and European  standardization committees.<br>
&nbsp;His main duties in this project are:</p>
                          <ul>
                            <li>Planning of project infrastructure  and time schedule</li>
                            <li>Coordination of the various  sections</li>
                            <li>Modelling and Simulation</li>
                          </ul>
                          <p>&nbsp;</p>
                          <p><strong>Marcus Hoffmann</strong>, Radon Competence Center â€“ SUPSI, Canobbio-Lugano, Switzerland.<br>
                            Marcus Hoffmann  got also a PhD in Physics and works as a researcher (especially in radon  issues), computer administrator and lecturer in mathematics at the <em>University of Applied Sciences and Arts of  Southern Switzerland</em> (SUPSI) in Ticino, the Italian Canton of Switzerland.  Experienced in a wide field of building remediation since 2008 he also took  part of several research programs funded by the Swiss National Science  Foundation (SNSF) and other national and international programs.<br>
                            His main duties  in this project are:</p>
                          <ul>
                            <li>Planning of project  infrastructure and time schedule</li>
                            <li>Coordination of the various  sections</li>
                            <li>Web administrator of the  homepage</li>
                          </ul>
                          <p>Besides these duties, he is also member of  the <em>Basic Research</em> and <em>Modelling &amp; Simulation</em> sections.</p></th>
